Delicious summer meal! I used frozen baby peas instead of beans, and it turned out quite well. Will definitely make this again!

Rating: 4
We really enjoyed this meal! I added alot of pepper and red pepper flakes which made it tangy and peppery. We really liked it!! Only used about a cup of the pasta water and simmered it for about 15min to get it a bit thicker. Didn't have Tagliatelle noodles so used Egg noodles. Can't wait to make it again!

Rating: 2
Hmmm. I wanted to love this. But the cream and water with lemon juice was runny and the cheese clumped all over the veggies. It never really became a sauce, ultimately and I think it needs more flavor than just cheese and veggies. Fresh herbs and/or garlic maybe. I'm going to check that I wouldn't make it again, but I may do so with a LOT of alterations to this recipe.

Rating: 3
As other reviewers have noted, this is fresh and bright. I used fresh haricots verts instead of frozen, adding them in with the zucchini and onions. I also used half-and-half instead of heavy cream to try to lighten it, and it worked nicely. This is a great basic recipe that could be changed to suit the contents of your fridge - the best kind of recipe!!

Rating: 4
This recipe makes you forget about the weary winter. I used a Mandolin to slice small zuccini and substituted 2 handfuls of petite peas for the beans & added fresh mushrooms. I finished the dish with additional grated fresh lemon peel on top. Light, with definition of the delicate flavor of each ingredient. A keeper for sure.

Rating: 4
Absolutely delicious. The flavors were clean and simple. I made home made pasta and added fresh shrimp I tossed with a little salt and pepper and lemon juice. Cooked until just pink and added last.

Rating: 4
I actually left the pasta out and made zucchini "ribbons" with asparagus pieces in the lemony cream sauce. Very nice for spring.

Rating: 4
This is a great tasting weeknight recipe. I made it exactly as described. The baby zucchini cook up very fast as I sliced them thinner than just halving them. The lemon makes this perfect for spring. Next time I will add other veggies I have on hand as I think the sauce goes well with just about any veggie.

Rating: 4
This was fantastic! It was satisfying but not too heavy and had a fresh, Spring-like flavor. I didn't use baby zucchini, I just sliced 2 regular zucchini into 1/4 in. thick slices. Otherwise, I made as written and was very pleased with the results.